Commit Message: added url of GitHub repo to setup.py, added docs homepage to RAEDME.md.
removed scripts, since we are now using entry_points instead of scripts.
forced version 2.4.1 for ruffus in install_requires due to the bug "https://github.com/bunbun/ruffus/issues/53" in its latest versions.
included LICENSE file and updated the version to upload to PyPi.
updated to evaluate the values when updatig SAMPLES and SHARED sections.
removed the limitation on the number of simultaneous jobs/pipelines.
added --no_prefix back to the input options.
changed the tab to space in the template component_reqs.py.
added Change log section to README.md.
added support for floating point mem requests.
added support for floating point mem requests.
Added individual requirements sub-section for each task.
added username and version to the newly created config files.
removed __GENERAL__ section since every task now has its own requirements subsection.
users can now specify the requirements of each task separately in the setup file.
put __GENERAL__ section back since often multiple tasks share the same requirements. TASK requirements subsection, however, takes precedence on GENERAL requirements.
made all the *MERGE* files go into a separate folder called "merge".
interval file now takes precedence over the synchronization.
added a check to make sure that the input of the implicit merge node is always a list.
added support for tags in the interval file.
bug fixes (where adding interval tags broke the sample connection for interval file).
added "tag" as a required input to node.copy() method.
fixed the bug that inflate/deflate could result in infinite loop.
added the functionality to switch on/off the implicit merge.
changed the default value of "merge" attribute to "True".
fixed the problem where multiple similar merges could happen. Now, each required implicit merge happens only once.
added a mechanism to update the requirements of the implicit merge via General section, KRONOS-82.
